<h1 id="baba-ganoosh">Baba Ganoosh</h1>

<h4 id="cooked-augergines-and-garlic">Cooked Augergines and garlic.</h4>

<ul>
  <li>Cooked aubergine flesh 
(From the karni yarik recipe or from one whole Augergine)</li>
  <li>2 Garlic cloves</li>
  <li>1/2 tbps Olive oil</li>
  <li>Salt and pepper</li>
</ul>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Blend the cooked aubergine and garlic or mash the cooked augergine, finely chop the garlic 
and mix well. Season with salt and pepper.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Put in a frying pan with the olive oil and keep it over a low heat for 10 - 15 minutes. Stir it regularly.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Serve with nice bread or rice or foor or whatever - it tastes good.</p>
  </li>
</ol>

